I bought this for a gift for a friend.  They liked it so much that I decieded to get one for myself.
I bought this for my 55&#34; Samsung LCD LED TV. I mounted it on a wall and intended to use it extended to 180 degrees. At the 180 degree extension, there is very noticeable tilt, which gets worse each day, until the TV is tilting sort of comically. If you are just using it to watch a TV &#34;head-on&#34; the tilt probably won't matter to you, but if you are using it at any sort of angle for a large TV you will have the tilt problem. The arm is simply not designed properly to handle the 180 degree extension.Also, if you are new to this TV mount thing, note that this VESA 400 compatible mount will not necessarily work for your VESA 400 compatible TV. I discovered that not all VESA 400 mounts work with all VESA 400 TVs. I had to &#34;improvise&#34; to get this mount to work and could not use any of the mounting configurations in the instruction booklet. This problem had no bearing on the &#34;tilt&#34; problem described above. I don't really understand what the point is of listing VESA compatibility when it doesn't seem to actually indicate compatibility, but there must be some tech guru who has a complex and useless explanation for it somewhere.Otherwise, the installation was fairly easy. In about two hours I was able to get this attached to my wall, where it immediately began it's slow drooping progress toward the floor. I wish I had just kept the TV sitting on a table.
Now that it is installed it is fine.  But installation was a pain.  Unlike other similar low priced mounts, this does not have a separate plate that you mount to the TV then mount to the bracket.  You have to hold the TV up in position, align with bracket holes and start screws.  Try that on ladders 6 feet in the air,  with a 40 or 50 pound TV.  I bought some screws of proper size, cut off the head and used 2 as locating guides to get screw holes aligned.  Started 2 screws then replace my starter studs with screws. Made it easier but NOT easy.  Also adjustment is very difficult with TV installed.  Weight of TV binds the adjusting bracket when you loosen set screw.  I would NOT recommend this mount there are better choices.  I got an OMNIBasics OBFM60 mount for a similar price ( on clearance) and it was 5 STARS compared to this.
