This stand holds up my hefty 40&#34; LCD TV quite well. I bought this mount because the new place I moved into built the studs too far apart for my other mount. This item seemed a little questionable, but I went with it because of the reviews. I'm glad I did! It isn't the sturdiest piece of equipment, but the TV doesn't sway around by itself and I'm not worrying about it whenever I leave the apartment. I don't know how well it would stand up to being run into or being in an earthquake, but then again if those are potential issues then maybe a wall mount isn't too ideal in the first place! The only thing that is a little inconvenient is the arm length. It will hold the TV out quite a ways from the wall, but it has trouble keeping the TV centered on the mounting stud while it's mostly compressed to the wall. Besides that, very good item.
