Highly recommend this product. Price is awesome and it includes an HDMI cable. This same "combo" at Walmart would run a good $150.Installed it in 30-45 minutes and the biggest pain for me was finding a stud in the wall. there are 6 holes for the lag screws to go into which are supposed to go into a stud in the wall. Well in my wall we were able to find half the stud, so 2 of the holes (one on the top right and one on the bottom right) went into a stud, the middle screw I think got part of the stud and the 2 left screws I had to use an anchor on. Probably not the best way of doing it, but the TV is up very sturdy. Now I don't move it around at all since the spot I mounted is a corner and doesn't allow for much movement, but if you get this unit and intend to adjust it constantly I recommend you install it into a solid stud.
