The only reason I didn't give this a 5-star review is one design flaw:  The mounting plate for the TV isn't intended to come off the main arm (as it is secured with a lock nut) to allow easy mounting.  In other words, you have to mount the system to a wall and then hoist your TV up while someone else fastens it to the mounting plate.  That said, it wasn't difficult to mount to a wall, nor was it too difficult to secure the TV and it is very sturdy.  I've mounted a 32" TV that weighs about 25 lbs. and think the mount could've easily handled another 30 lbs.  I received the item within a few days of ordering and am quite pleased with the product.  Even at Sam's Club, mounts of this quality cost at least twice as much.
