I checked around Amazon as well as some other sites, and decided these were what I needed.  I read the reviews, looked at the pictures and bought two of these.  I received them today.  I unpacked one of them, read the instructions and immediately filled out the return request for Amazon.  These mounts are very, very heavy and require 6, yes SIX, screws to mount to the wall.  Are you kidding me?  The TVs are only 22 lbs!  Two screws in the studs and then more damage to the wall than is necessary.  What a joke!  And Lag bolts?  Ever heard of screws?  The other issue is that these are very hard to move.  I bought an articulating wall mount for a reason, and I expect them to be able to move without a wrench in my hand.
It's hard to argue with this mount for the price.  It's an excellent value and sturdy.  I mounted a 32" LG set that weighs about 17 lbs and did not experience any sag.  The instructions do not indicate this, but I removed the TV plate and the wall bracket from the arms to facilitate installation.  My LG set has a 200mm x 100mm mount pattern.  The M4 screws are the correct choice for my application, but I needed washers to prevent the screw heads from passing through the large holes in the plate.  There are some spacers/washers included in the hardware pack, but I decided to pick up 4 fender washers and used those instead.  After I got the plate mounted to the TV and the wall bracket mounted, I reattached the arms to the TV bracket and re-installed the bolt I removed earlier.  I had a helper install the bolt attaching the arm to the wall plate while I held onto the TV.  Once I got everything tightened up, I was a bit concerned that the set was crooked even though I installed the wall bracket level and plum.  Luckily there is about 5 degrees of rotation adjustment in this mount which will remedy any slight rotation issues.  I'm very happy with this product and feel it is an outstanding value.
