This mount is best used if the TV needs to extend away from the wall or be rotated so it is not parallel with the mounting wall.  The mount I received was exactly as described.  "Fits VESA (mounting hole patterns) 100x100 200x100  200x200mm without extender, and also fits VESA  600x400  400x400  600x300  400x200  300x300mm with 4 plate extender:  loading capacity up to 66 lbs;  VESA TV plate can be taken off, quick release design for easy installation;  Standard hardware and user manual included."  The enclosed mounting hardware was sufficient to attach the wall mount to wood studs or masonry walls, and there is an assortment of  screws to attach the TV plate to the back of most TVs.  The wall plate also has a plastic cover that snaps on and hides the mounting bolts, giving the wall mounting plate a "finished look."  The included instructions were well written, detailed and describe the mounting process in step by step fashion. (In my opinion, some of the best instructions I have seen for the half-dozen mounts I have installed.)  One definitely needs a stud sensor, electric drill and a good wrench to install the mount.  I used the mount on an older 42 inch plasma that weighs 60 lbs, so it will handle its rated weight, assuming both mounting bolts of the wall plate are properly secured in studs.  I have observed no "sagging," but I would say the arm "flexes"  about 1 inch with my 60 lb TV attached and the arm fully extended.  In summary, I rate it 5 stars, and feel this is an excellent mount for the money, especially if one has a heavier (40-60 lb) TV with VESA mounting holes larger than 200x200.
