Someone gave me this book at my baby shower. Five years and two kids later, it's still a favorite! The text offers a sweet, rhyming lullaby, perfect for bedtime rituals. The die-cut pages and 3-D glittery butterflies provide counting fun and visual appeal. It teaches numbers, colors and subtraction. And it's sturdy! At first glance it seems feminine, but my very rough-and-tumble son enjoys it as well.This is a great book -- the only gift I received that day that isn't collecting dust.
